Here's a PlantUML sequence diagram representing the control flow of the Algorithm Visualization Application:

```plantuml
@startuml YW-Ma_Algorithms-Visualizer

actor User
participant "React Frontend" as Frontend
participant "Sidebar" as Sidebar
participant "Map" as Map
participant "GraphSVG" as GraphSVG
participant "GraphTable" as GraphTable
participant "EventProxy" as EventProxy
participant "Node.js Backend" as Backend
participant "C++ Executable" as CPP
database "MySQL Database" as DB

User -> Frontend : Access application
Frontend -> Sidebar : Render sidebar
Frontend -> Map : Initialize map (BMap API)
Frontend -> GraphSVG : Initialize graph visualization
Frontend -> GraphTable : Initialize graph table

User -> Sidebar : Select algorithm
Sidebar -> Backend : Request algorithm execution
Backend -> CPP : Execute algorithm
CPP -> Backend : Return algorithm steps
Backend -> DB : Store algorithm steps
Backend -> Frontend : Send algorithm data

Frontend -> EventProxy : Publish algorithm data
EventProxy -> GraphSVG : Update graph visualization
EventProxy -> GraphTable : Update table data

User -> Map : Interact with map
Map -> Backend : Send map interaction data
Backend -> DB : Store map state

User -> Sidebar : Add/Delete node
Sidebar -> Backend : Update graph data
Backend -> DB : Persist graph changes
Backend -> Frontend : Send updated graph data

Frontend -> EventProxy : Publish graph update
EventProxy -> GraphSVG : Redraw graph
EventProxy -> GraphTable : Update table

User -> Frontend : Request report
Frontend -> Backend : Fetch report data
Backend -> DB : Retrieve report data
Backend -> Frontend : Send report data
Frontend -> User : Display report

@enduml
```